# Browser Debugging Network Restriction

When using browser tools for local debugging:

- Only navigate to `http://localhost:<port>` or `http://127.0.0.1:<port>`.
- Never use LAN/private network addresses such as `10.x.x.x`, `172.16-31.x.x`, `192.168.x.x`, or `*.local`.
- Never expose or rely on development servers bound for LAN access during debugging.
- Do not start dev servers with `--host 0.0.0.0` (or equivalent LAN binding). Prefer default host or explicit localhost binding.

If a local page does not load on `localhost`, fix the local dev-server setup first, then continue using localhost URLs only.
